addInnerEdge

void addInnerEdge(CyEdge edge)
Add a new inner edge to this group. An inner edge is defined as an edge that only connects nodes that are members of the group.

Parameters:
edge - the inner edge to add.

addNode

void addNode(CyNode node)
Add a new node to the group. This will also iterate through all of the edges associated with this node and assign them as inner or outer edges.

Parameters:
node - the node to be added

addOuterEdge

void addOuterEdge(CyEdge edge)
Add a new outer edge to this group. An outer edge is defined as an edge where at least one nodes that it connects to is not a member of this group.

Parameters:
edge - the outer edge to add.
